args: It beggars belief the imperials would come\nso far in pursuit of fleeing villagers.
Prince, we still have elderly and children\nwho are lagging behind!
But we can't just leave these folks here\nwhile we go back for the stragglers.
You may entrust them to me.
O power universal! Fire of the nine\nflames, stone of destruction, let thy\nforce be manifest!
Come now, all of you!\nWhile they are scattered!
And YOU will go no further. Haaaah!
If you insist on continuing such unjust\nbehavior, I shall teach you firsthand the\ntrue value of the Qilin's secrets.
None of us will soon forget this kindness.
Think naught of it; I did only what anyone\nwould. Now let us head for the Halidom.
What are you doing, Xuan Zang?!
I am called Fa Ming, and you have my\ndeepest gratitude for seeing to my\nbumbling pupil.
Actually, she's been a huge help to us.
Which is proof of her failure!
You understand, do you not, Xuan Zang?\nExplain it yourself.

The Qilin civilization flourished in the
distant past, where their magical society
attained vast heights and allowed the
people to live lives of plenty.

However, their ambitions reached too far,
and their spirits fell into wretchedness.
As a result, they invited great calamity
upon the world, leading to its ruin.
The few surviving Qilin took precautions to\nensure such a calamity would never again\nbe visited upon the world.
Thus, it is forbidden for a Qilin sealer\nto interact with outsiders.
The relics of our people are beyond the\nken of the modern world, and sealers\nare tasked with their disposal.
If you aid this prince, his victory over\nthe Empire may well come to pass.
However, he is a man who stands\nat the very forefront of history.

If you stay at his side, the Qilin's skills
will doubtless find their way into the light
once more, thus bringing about a repeat
of the ancient Qilin's ruination!
And is it not your exact duty, Xuan Zang,\nto make certain such a thing does NOT\ncome to pass?!
How can you call yourself a sealer?!
Aw, hell! Them pig-headed imperials are\nback AGAIN! They're attackin' one of the\nvillages near the forest!
Did you hear nothing I said, Xuan Zang?!
Yes, master. I heard you very well.
And I have not forgotten my duty\nas a sealer.
But that does not mean I can turn a blind\neye to the suffering of others!
Bah! A handful of lives are meaningless\nwhen compared to the great river of time!\nI thought you smarter than this...
